# Environment Variables Guide

## Required Variables

### Server Configuration
- `PORT` - Port number for the server (default: 8000)
- `BASE_URL` - Full base URL for shortened links (e.g., http://localhost:8000 or https://yourdomain.com)

### Database Configuration
- `MONGODB_URI` - MongoDB connection string (default: mongodb://localhost:27017/shortUrl)

## Usage

1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env`
2. Update the values according to your environment
3. Restart the server

## Example Configurations

### Local Development
```
PORT=8000
BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/shortUrl
```

### Production
```
PORT=3000
BASE_URL=https://short.yourdomain.com
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/shortUrl
```

## Security Note
Never commit `.env` file to version control!
